ad_text:
Muuun Hotel is the latest building to feature in Dezeen and Kia’s video series highlighting contemporary South Korean architecture.

Located in the city of Gyeongju, South Korea, Muuun Hotel was designed by local practices Nomal and Onjuim Housing Studio.

The hotel combines contemporary architectural elements with features typical of a South Korean hanok (or traditional Korean house) such as a vernacular tiled roof and exposed wood ceiling beams. 

Dezeen has paired Muuun Hotel with Kia’s EV3, an all-electric compact SUV, which features in the video alongside the building. The Kia EV3 sports a minimal appearance at its front and rear with headlights that emerge from vertical slits and linear tail lights.

Video produced by Dezeen.

Click the link in bio to read more.

ad_text:
Muuun Hotel is the latest building to feature in Dezeen and Kia’s video series highlighting contemporary South Korean architecture.

Located in the city of Gyeongju, South Korea, Muuun Hotel was designed by local practices Nomal and Onjuim Housing Studio.

The hotel combines contemporary architectural elements with features typical of a South Korean hanok (or traditional Korean house) such as a vernacular tiled roof and exposed wood ceiling beams. 

Dezeen has paired Muuun Hotel with Kia’s EV3, an all-electric compact SUV, which features in the video alongside the building. The Kia EV3 sports a minimal appearance at its front and rear with headlights that emerge from vertical slits and linear tail lights.

Video produced by Dezeen.

Click the link in bio to read more.

#Kia #Design #EV3

#paidpartnership

ad_text:
Muuun Hotel is the latest building to feature in Dezeen and Kia’s video series highlighting contemporary South Korean architecture.

Located in the city of Gyeongju, South Korea, Muuun Hotel was designed by local practices Nomal and Onjuim Housing Studio.

The hotel combines contemporary architectural elements with features typical of a South Korean hanok (or traditional Korean house) such as a vernacular tiled roof and exposed wood ceiling beams. 

Dezeen has paired Muuun Hotel with Kia’s EV3, an all-electric compact SUV, which features in the video alongside the building. The Kia EV3 sports a minimal appearance at its front and rear with headlights that emerge from vertical slits and linear tail lights.

Video produced by Dezeen.

Click the link in bio to read more.

#Kia #Design #EV3

#paidpartnership

ad_text:
Muuun Hotel is the latest building to feature in Dezeen and Kia’s video series highlighting contemporary South Korean architecture.

Located in the city of Gyeongju, South Korea, Muuun Hotel was designed by local practices Nomal and Onjuim Housing Studio.

The hotel combines contemporary architectural elements with features typical of a South Korean hanok (or traditional Korean house) such as a vernacular tiled roof and exposed wood ceiling beams. 

Dezeen has paired Muuun Hotel with Kia’s EV3, an all-electric compact SUV, which features in the video alongside the building. The Kia EV3 sports a minimal appearance at its front and rear with headlights that emerge from vertical slits and linear tail lights.

Video produced by Dezeen.

Click the link in bio to read more.

#Kia #Design #EV3

#paidpartnership

ad_text:
Muuun Hotel is the latest building to feature in Dezeen and Kia’s video series highlighting contemporary South Korean architecture.

Located in the city of Gyeongju, South Korea, Muuun Hotel was designed by local practices Nomal and Onjuim Housing Studio.

The hotel combines contemporary architectural elements with features typical of a South Korean hanok (or traditional Korean house) such as a vernacular tiled roof and exposed wood ceiling beams. 

Dezeen has paired Muuun Hotel with Kia’s EV3, an all-electric compact SUV, which features in the video alongside the building. The Kia EV3 sports a minimal appearance at its front and rear with headlights that emerge from vertical slits and linear tail lights.

Video produced by Dezeen.
